frameDefinitions: This frame is about Items in the state of occupying a certain Rank within a hierarchy.
A Figure is characterized as near the Ground, according to some contextually given scale.
An Agent causes an Impactor to make sudden, forcible contact with an Impactee, or manipulates two (or more) Impactors so that they make mutual forcible contact.
A Place is located far off from centers of population, culture, and/or trade.
An Agent, by virtue of strength or forcefulness, controls, rules, or strongly influences some Patient in some Situation.

An Item is located at the top end of a scale of importance or social rank (or some other Attribute) in comparison to other members of a Contrast_set (usually, implicit) that is otherwise similar in kind to the Item.
frameExamples: He <t>ranks</t> second in his class in mathematics.
She put her shoes <t>under</t> the table .
He <t>slammed</t> his fist down on the table and bellowed something unintelligible.
The fireballing righthander looked poised to <t>dominate</t> the Yankees yet again, striking out seven straight batters during one stretch
The <t>main</t> problem is that the administration has not yet clarified 'Regime change.' INI
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Rank</fen> which the <fen>Item</fen> occupies.
The Item which occupies the Rank in the hierarchy.
The dimension along which the ranking is defined.
The time at which/period over which the <fen>Item</fen> occupies the <fen>Rank</fen>
The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The figure can be an entity or an event.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.
The <fen>Impactee</fen> is the entity which is hit by the <fen>Impactor</fen>.
The <fen>Impactor</fen> is the entity that hits the <fen>Impactee</fen> because of the <fen>Agent</fen>'s efforts.
The <fen>Impactors</fen> are the multiple entities that collide.
The <fen>Agent</fen>  causes an impact.

The <fen>Cause</fen> marks expressions that indicate some non-intentional, 
typically non-human, force that causes an <fen>Impactor</fen> to make sudden, 
forcible contact with an Impactee.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen>  when the impact occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The town or area that is in a remote location.
The <fen>Agent</fen> controls the Patient by being forceful and possibly aggressive.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is trying to gain control of a situation, but ends up being subject to the control and influence of the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The time when the domination takes place.
The place where the domination occurs.
An <fen>Item</fen> is the foremost thing in the <fen>Contrast_set</fen>.
This role identifies the domain (usually temporally or spatially defined) within which the <fen>Item</fen> is primary among its kind.
The <fen>Contrast_set</fen> is a group of entities similar to the <fen>Item</fen> out of which the <fen>Item</fen> is the most preeminent.
